Author: nft_world
Content: @vexy  As an alternative point of view, buying land near plazas and roads is expensive and no one uses them anyway (people teleport). Buying near plazas and roads also limits your ability to expand. And chances are, your neighbors are investors who are just waiting for an opportunity to flip their land (leaving it empty in the meantime). Some good alternative advice to consider is buying in areas near content creators, where events are being hosted regularly, and where you might have opportunity to expand your estate later on if you so desire

Author: kaze_no_kai
Content:
:dcl: Hi All, Please note that today (27th) at 1pm (UTC) all of our dapps will start using version 2 of Wallet Connect. 
This version change was an effort all wallets and dapps on the ecosystem had to face due to the shutdown of version 1 of Wallet Connect, which happens the 28th of June at 2pm (UTC).

The only user facing change is that the QR that has to be scanned with the mobile wallet will look different.

Please make sure your mobile wallets are up to date by updating them through their respective Android/iOS stores to avoid any connection issues.

Please let us know in case you notice any issues ð ð

Author: draconicfeathers
Content: Hi guys! I'm new here! I intend to be a content creator and VJ and perform and do fun creative things, but I cant seem to connect my metamask wallet to the EXE/App on my PC; I scan with my phone app and nothing happens. I can log in though the browser but I'd rather get in via the app. Any tips?

Author: _cicadaa_
Content: Hi, @DraconicFeathers. This situation sometimes happens to me as well, and restarting the Desktop app a few times usually does the trick. You may also want to reinstall the app as a possible fix for the issue. Please give these a shot and let me know how it goes.

Author: draconicfeathers
Content: whats supposed to happen if it does work?

Author: _cicadaa_
Content: After scanning the QR code, you should receive a prompt on your wallet to sign and authorize the sign-in attempt. After that, the Decentraland app should automatically load and log you into your account. Also, please make sure that your MetaMask mobile wallet app is updated (version 7.1.0).

Author: draconicfeathers
Content: so reinstalling metamask on my phone did the job actually, thanks so much!

Author: _cicadaa_
Content: Hello, @NFT eve. This is possible. However, please note that if someone rents your space, they're actually renting your LAND. Meaning, they will have the operator's permission to make changes to the LAND and scene deployed on it (https://docs.decentraland.org/player/market/rentals/). That being said and in my own opinion, it wouldn't be the best way to generate income from your LAND.

Author: foomanxc.c.c.
Content:
Whatâs goin on fellow Decntralandians! My name is Will AKA Fooman and I am the co founder of the Crypto Chicken Collective. As many of you are well aware our project got the funding frozen/revoked about eight months ago due to our project being behind schedule. Shortly after that time, the DCL community decided it was best to hold off on granting or resuming funding to projects which we animatedly agreed with. Hector (the other co founder) and I decided to start our own businesses IRL at this point as money never sleeps. Now that we have those businesses up and running we feel like we have the time and energy that this project deserves. 
I will attach a doc that will show all transactions made with the $39,236 we received in funding. 
The aim of sharing this information is to instill faith in the community that we do what we say we are going to do (even if it takes a while). 
Additionally we would like to share what we have and where we are looking to go with the community on one of the next couple town halls. It will be at this time that the community will be able to see that we  are in fact largely in compliance with our original grant guidelines (fell short by 500 twitter followers). 
Letâs get the wheels in motion on this thing and finally battle some cocxð

Author: foomanxc.c.c.
Content: Iâm not sure they will be able to help with this unfortunatelyð I appreciate the gesture though!

Author: a.t8201
Content: i just downloaded the game didn't bother customising my avatr  but im on my laptop and using a,s,w,d it won't move at all, my laptop is an msi one and the server looked rather blank purple sky and ornage grided floor

When buying land u can use the builder for a feel of how large u need. Builder is found on the upper left corner of the official DCL webpage. Start with a scene of 1x1. There are height limits as well. Most p2e games are not worth your time if you are playing just to earn money. What I mean is that if you spend an hour on the game and expect to earn what u could in the real world for an hour u'd be very disappointed.

Don't see DCL as a game itself, but rather a 3d webpage. There are scenes that contain games, scenes that play movies, contain an nft gallery and others that hold events. It's pretty much up to you as to what u want to do with your land

Author: nft_world
Content: @Zom.eth #help is a pretty generic channel. If you want to learn how to make wearables, #3d-modeling is better. There is also #builder-and-3d, #sdk and others. But these arenât workshops with dedicated support. Building in DCL requires a lot of initiative on your part. Check the docs (https://docs.decentraland.org/creator/), search YouTube for videos, and feel free to browse repositories such as Awesome Repository (https://github.com/decentraland-scenes/Awesome-Repository). And keep an eye out for public events and livestreams as well. There are plenty of resources if you ask around (nicely) ð But it does take some time to build these skills unfortunately

Author: cheddarqueso
Content: Hoolaa. I would say to start by choosing what type of land are you looking for... something by a road or plaza, or in a district? Then look at similar  lands that have sold recently. This will help you get an idea of the current market price for the type of land you are looking for. Then start looking for lands that are listed for sale... and make offers based on your budget... negotiate. You can almost always buy for cheaper than the listing price. Hope this helps and know that this is not financial advice. Also speak to others and formulate your own path. Good luck. ð

Author: zigg.
Content: Howdy! I've noticed your inquiries regarding Linked wearables. For a deeper understanding of this topic, I strongly recommend visiting the following document: https://docs.decentraland.org/creator/wearables/linked-wearables/

Author: jun8496
Content:
thank you for your guidance, but there are still something unclear for me to understand:

1. Will the linked wearable be automatically acquired on Decentraland at the same time as the NFT is acquired? Or is there an additional process to acquire them?

2. If I resell an NFT after acquiring it, is the linked wearable still valid on decentraland?

Author: zigg.
Content: Decentraland's linked wearables are acquired independently of their associated NFTs. To utilize them, you must follow distinct procedures, which can differ depending on the NFT. In essence, linked wearables are not automatically bundled with NFTs; an extra step is typically necessary to employ them in the virtual world. Additionaly, when you sell an NFT in Decentraland, the linked wearable typically passes on to the new owner. However, it's essential to review the NFT's terms, as some may impose transfer limitations. Please refer to the document I shared and examine NFT listings for specifics on linked wearables.

Author: posttokesmoke
Content:
Decentraland, a blockchain-based virtual world, was poised to ride the wave of excitement surrounding blockchain technology, virtual reality, and decentralized metaverses. However, it failed to capture the moment of its initial popularity and often comes across as boring for several reasons.

Firstly, technical hurdles like navigation issues and complex blockchain processes hindered accessibility and frustrated users. The lack of engaging experiences within the platform, despite the promise of user-generated content, left users searching for meaningful interactions.

Influential figures like PeanutButta, despite bringing attention to Decentraland, failed to fulfill their promises of transforming it into a hub of creativity and excitement. Their impact on the platform's vibrancy and engagement was limited.

The creative void within Decentraland, characterized by uninspiring content and a lack of social interaction, contributed to its perceived boredom. The high entry costs associated with owning virtual real estate and the risk aversion to blockchain technology acted as financial barriers, limiting user diversity.

Additionally, Decentraland's community often felt stagnant, with gated communities segregating the user base. This lack of an active and engaged community further added to the platform's dull reputation.

In conclusion, Decentraland's failure to capitalize on its initial hype, coupled with technical challenges, limited engagement, unfulfilled promises from influencers, economic barriers, and a stagnant community, has led to its reputation as a boring virtual world. To overcome this, Decentraland must improve user experiences, foster a vibrant community, and enhance accessibility and excitement to fulfill its potential as a thriving decentralized metaverse.

Lots of places. The main focal points are OMI's Discord server and on GitHub repositories (both OMI and non-OMI repositories, like those from Microsoft, Khronos, etc).
I am doing my best to reach out to more communities to discuss this, because I've found that it can be difficult to get people to leave their comfort zone (ex: their usual Discord server). But here are some links:
OMI group's website with links to Discord and GitHub: <https://omigroup.org/>
OMI glTF repository <https://github.com/omigroup/gltf-extensions>
Microsoft glTF physics repository <https://github.com/eoineoineoin/glTF_Physics>
Khronos glTF repository <https://github.com/KhronosGroup/glTF>

Author: akhavan894358
Content: @chastain How to sell them in Dicentraland? please guide me

Author: chastain06
Content:
In order to sell them in the Marketplace in Decentraland,

First, you need to create a collection. Please see this article for full steps and guides on how to create a collection: https://docs.decentraland.org/creator/wearables-and-emotes/manage-collections/creating-collection/.

Then, once a collection is created, the wearables need to be uploaded. Please see these articles on how to upload the following:
Wearables: https://docs.decentraland.org/creator/wearables-and-emotes/manage-collections/uploading-wearables/
Emotes: https://docs.decentraland.org/creator/wearables-and-emotes/manage-collections/uploading-emotes/
Smart wearables: https://docs.decentraland.org/creator/wearables-and-emotes/manage-collections/uploading-smart-wearables/

After uploading, the collection needs to be published. Please see this article to learn more about how to publish a collection: https://docs.decentraland.org/creator/wearables/publishing-collections/.

Lastly, you need to wait for the curation committee to approve your collections. Once approved, you can now sell it in the Marketplace. To learn more about the Curation Committee, you can check this article: https://docs.decentraland.org/creator/wearables/curation-committee/.

Author: metaversecrypto.
Content:
Hi hi I'm sure ever1 knows the Apple Vision Pro XR is coming out in 3 to 6 months. Is decentraland gonna be ready?

Is this game built with Unity? I see Apple VR partnered with unity so devs can build apps for it

Author: zigg.
Content:
Howdy!  I understand that you're inquiring about the compatibility of the Apple Vision Pro XR with Decentraland and whether Decentraland was built using the Unity game engine. Regarding your question about VR compatibility, at this time, Decentraland does not have official support for any VR headset.

Nonetheless, there is a committed team that received funding from the DAO for their proposal aimed at enabling VR usage (you can find their proposal here: https://governance.decentraland.org/proposal/?id=088fc210-5e26-11ec-8188-4352ce3d30e7), and they are actively advancing their work in this area. Alpha-testing is currently underway. To access more details and the latest VR build, you can visit this channel: https://discord.com/channels/894658869391933540/936190478003634176. Please note that joining the Decentraland DAO Discord may be necessary, and you can do so via this link: https://discord.com/invite/ZdzKgYE5Q3.

Additionally, Decentraland was indeed developed using the Unity game engine.

Content: Hello how are you?I have seen a lot of people making big profits with trading and even quitting their jobs.I want to be like them also.Can you help me achieve that?

Author: chastain06
Content:
Hello @willy.apaza! You can earn MANA by doing the following:

1. LAND - If you purchased a LAND or estate, you can rent it to scene developers who do not own a LAND. This way, you'll be able to earn from it. You can check the Marketplace for renting LANDS: https://market.decentraland.org/.
2. Wearables - You can create and publish clothes and other wearables in the Marketplace.
3. Participate in the Events - You can participate in some events that reward wearables you can resell at the marketplace. Please note that not every event offers rewards. You can check this link for the Events that may interest you: https://events.decentraland.org/.

Author: rick603
Content: So itâs possible to host your own decentraland server? If for whatever reason decentraland folded as a company the community could keep it going?

Author: mattimus
Content: It is designed to fold. The funding from the mana contract for the foundation ends after 10 years which we are 3 or 4 years into. Yes everything is meant to be open source, smart contracts on eth and polygon will live "forever" and community is enabled to keep it going. It is considered more of a protocol than an application or company

Author: rick603
Content: Design wise though it could be a virtual world and survive without the cryptocurrency side of things. But itâs nice that itâs open source, lot of good projects seem to fold without that

Author: mattimus
Content: After than any funds the Dao has remaining can sustain community funding but anyone can run a catalyst, the server which contains all of the scenes files, and run their own explorer/client, the app which loads the scenes and let's you explore them.

Author: mattimus
Content: The land parcels for genesis city, names and wearables will always exist as nfts as long as eth and polygon live but you could technically run your own decentraland without the crypto validation parts

Content: I think a nice playground would be nice where everything is free, but that wouldnât be profitable lol

Author: proteo4934
Content:
I had the same problem, with a slow connection. It is most likely due to this:
https://docs.decentraland.org/creator/development-guide/sdk7/network-connections/#request-timeout
The designers of the Sophia scene seem to not have heeded the advice from here:
https://docs.decentraland.org/creator/development-guide/performance-optimization/
There are two videos there which can push the loading time of that specific scene-within-a-scene beyond 30 seconds, and that appears to timeout the loading of *many* other components in other scenes, including the coins.

Author: proteo4934
Content:
@twood@Kaze_no_Kai
Here's how I fixed it:
1) Finding `unity-renderer-windows.exe` in the Details section of the Task Manager, and setting its Priority to Realtime.
2) Setting the Scenes Load Radius to 1 in the app.
3) Walking out of the AI scene entrance, and back in.
4) Observing the network activity of `unity-renderer-windows.exe` in the Processes section of the Task Manager.
5) It usually stopped downloading after around 30 seconds. If stuff hadn't all loaded at that point, I'd go back to step 3). I had to do this a handful of times for each of the AI scenes !
6) Coins, road tiles, and buildings finally got loaded ð

Author: proteo4934
Content: Nevertheless, the Sophia scene itself does not ever fully load. No matter how often I step in that one, many parts of the building don't make it, I can see the network activity stop right as the (very impressive) videos finally show up in the scene, after significantly more than 30 seconds, so this is very likely to be the culprit of this issue, which no doubt has spurred away many of the newcomers who decided to visit Decentraland after hearing about the AI World Fair ð

Author: kaze_no_kai
Content:
Hey All ( @Proteus @Saus @DOCTORdripp @NikkiFuego ) as Kim already mentioned, we are truly sorry for all the hustle some updates cause the community, specially if it affects scenes in a negative way (e.g. something not working after an update). PB and _Ciacadaa mentioned some details may be lost in the general chat, but i totally get that people simply what to speak their mind specially if they had to fix stuff on their end or something was not working as expected after an update. Given that the Support team, which i am responsible for, handles the majority of the issues and updates in Discord and not only, i have a suggestion that may be a quick win for all of us:

ð¥  - We will update the roadmap channel under "Important" with all new stuff that are planned for the Q so you are aware what may be released in the near future
ð¥  - We will create a new channel "coming soon" to share the new stuff that we plan to make live in the next 1-2 weeks so you are aware
ð¥  - We will make sure the release notes are shared the moment we have all new stuff in place (it may be 1-2 days after a feature was released)

Lastly from our end we will keep close connection with Dev teams to make sure we are aware if any features may require any changes on your end so we can properly and timely communicate that.

Of course this may not be 100% bulletproof, but it is a step in the right direction.

Let me know how you feel about this approach and if it is aligned with your expectation.

Sorry for the long message and thanks in advance for the patience and understanding ð

Author: dogman1270

Author: kimbonft
Content:
Hey @dogman thanks for the question! To clarify, the application is open to anyone and those applications are reviewed independently from the scholarship need. If you are selected to attend the Summit, you are welcome to attend all events. 

The scholarship will be a separate application should the proposal be approved. This would be to cover flights for those that may need some financial assistance to get to Argentina. There is a question on the application "If selected, can you confirm you will be able to cover travel expenses (airfare, transportation from your home to airport, etc.)?" If you do NOT plan to apply for the scholarship for that flight assistance, you can just select "Yes, I confirm I will be able to cover travel expenses."

Author: kimbonft
Content: @Fancy you're more than welcome to apply as an active community member if the Summit is of interest to you!

Author: dogman1270
Content: Ok so just to be clear we need to be approved to come to the events at all?

Author: kimbonft
Content:
ok don't know what I just did there with the thread thing! 

But yes, it is an invite-only event based on applications rather than general open to public where people can purchase tickets

Author: dogman1270
Content: Its ok! Wow thats a bit surprising, how many people will be accepted and who is choosing who will come?

Author: kimbonft
Content:
Final numbers will be dependent on total applications. The intention is to make it more of an intimate gathering for the community as a celebration and an opportunity to all collaborate. All of the details are in the blog but it is a committee made up of Foundation leadership + Gino and Pablo from the community. 

https://decentraland.org/blog/announcements/announcing-the-decentraland-community-summit

Author: dogman1270
Content: I read the blog post and saw the application requires doxxing

Author: kimbonft
Content: Yes, given in the person nature of the event, we would need to have the attendee's information on the Foundation side for hotel bookings etc. so I understand that may be a reason for some to not attend and respect that decision. We will do every best effort on the foundation side to keep that information confidential and use DCL names throughout the event so publicly doxxing isn't required.

Author: dogman1270

Content: Great question. We didn't discuss that situation so let me find out. You would need to submit an application and be approved (using your DCL name), but I can confirm here for you all.

Author: kimbonft
Content: Totally understand that sentiment of it feeling like more of a process than a normal conference. The intention is NOT to exclude members of the community in any way but rather put a process in place to ensure it's the engaged and core community members joining to have that intimate feel and more small group opportunities to connect.

Author: dogman1270
Content: Tbh i think anyone who has stuck around for the bear market is a core community member. To me this feels more exclusionary than anything. Who would want to fly all the way to argentina if they are not engaged w the community?

Author: kimbonft
Content: Agree, those willing to make the trip and give their time and energy are definitely part of the core community here! The application process is a helpful way for us to understand demand, get a gauge on who is interested (what types of builders, etc.) while also giving back since the Foundation is primarily funding the Summit rather than asking everyone to pay for all of the travel, summit tickets, and all event activities.

Author: dogman1270
Content: This is a bit confusing. If the foundation is funding travel,tickets, etc. then why is there a dao grant for the same thing. My apologies i may be misunderstanding

Author: kimbonft
Content:
Happy to clarify -- all details pulled from the blog. 

The following costs will be covered for ALL applicants that are invited to the Summit. 
- Transportation to and from the Argentinian airport to the Summit location
- Hotel accommodations (double occupancy)
- Food and beverages during the Summit
- Planned social activities

However, attendees will be responsible for covering all travel expenses to Argentina and any additional expenses they incur throughout the 3-day event, outside of planned programming. --- The DAO grant is for a scholarships fund to help cover flights for those that may need it to make the event even more accessible for members of the community.

Author: dogman1270

Author: kimbonft
Content: Or they could chose to upgrade and just pay the difference (all of these details will be sent out to selected applicants with exact amount)

Author: kimbonft
Content: Definitely welcome to apply - I wouldn't worry about taking someone's spot. We are going to do our best effort to make space for those interested and have a good mix of contributors.

Author: bonna8
Content: can someone explain to me what dissolved estates are? is that still something that can happen? as in: can it happen that i put an offer on an parcel and that parcel gets dissolved and my offer accepted? and im stuck with something unusable?

Author: _cicadaa_
Content: Hi there, @bonna. Welcome to our official Discord server. Dissolved estates are still tokens on the Blockchain since they don't get burnt. That means any previous estates that have been dissolved will always have a token. Depending on the platform you use to buy NFTs, you could potentially buy a useless token. But that shouldn't happen on our official Marketplace (https://market.decentraland.org). That said, we highly suggest using our official Marketplace instead of purchasing LAND on other platforms.

Author: catadecruz
Content:
The district feature was removed 2+ years ago from the website due to lack of usage and maintenance. However, you can see your district contributions here: https://api.decentraland.org/v2/addresses/ETHADDRESS/contributions, please exchange **ETHADDRESS** with your address and make sure its lower case only. 

The result will show you the amount of LAND you have contributed to the according district, which is stated via its district ID. You can then use the district ID and find out what district it is here: https://api.decentraland.org/v2/districts/DISTRICTID by exchanging **DISTRICTID** with the ID you want to check.

Author: catadecruz
Content: That being said, the Decentraland Foundation is not associated with districts or their decision making. Depending on the district you aim to contact, they may have a website, Discord or other ways of contact, as long as the district hasnât been dissolved and is still active.

Author: catadecruz
Content: The dApps team generally looks into linked wearables. But the project itself does need to provide crucial information as well in order to get it running and into DCL. Depending on any impact of an issue/information you are looking for, the support team would be a good starting point generally. Once a linked wearables collection has been voted on via DAO, there will be a dedicated slack channel with the Foundation team to tackle further needed information/issues. Depending on the state/progress that has been made on a collection, there is more simple ways to skip the support team. But that depends on the project itself.

Author: proteo4934
Content:
Hear ye, hear ye ! Gather 'round to hear this tale of mine centered around the universe of Decentraland :dcl: 

I trekked all the way out to this far Far West on my trusted steed TopLap ð´ð», on the enthralling heedings of the AI World Fair announcements. 
How dismayed was I to find a place with barely any content, and full of ghosts ð«¥

A few elements of the surroundings did appear... And some UI widgets, alluding to the presence of coins, which presumably were lying around, nicely firing up the ole' scavenger instincts.

But no coin was to be seen !

And then there were some strange green walls which glowed for half a minute, after which they dropped away, supposedly indicating that content within had finished loading and was ready for entry. But... wait for it ! wait for it !
Oh you guessed it ?
Barely any content inside.

I left !

Author: proteo4934
Content:
Nevertheless I was fortunate to have connected that day with a member of the community who sounded surprised that I wasn't seeing content.
Otherwise I would have given up, concluding that DCL "just doesn't work"â¢

Instead I came back the next day, and tinkered with the Scenes Radius settings, contrasting them with TopLap's network activity, until I managed to get individual scenes to load.
It was quite gratifying to see the coins *finally* appear â-ðªððª-â

And then I was also able to see other avatars, and attend the AI World Fair, and really get a feel for what DCL is all about.

There's a lot of fixing up to do.
But I do believe it can get big.

Author: proteo4934
Content:
And so I would like to bring your attention to the initial deadly problem I encountered. The first trains I boarded with TopLap just didn't get there: the response after scanning the QR code with Metamask.
After a series of unsuccessful attempted fixes, one of the scans finally worked, and then the login was cached, so the issue was gone for a while.
But it showed up again when I tried to push a creation to the test world for the first time.
I tried, and tried, and tried, and it just wouldn't complete successfully !
And then out of desperation I tried to push a blank scene to the Main world. It worked ð
And at the same time, the answer to the cause of problem showed up.

Author: proteo4934
Content: The times listed by all the catalysts were 1-2 minutes behind.

Author: proteo4934
Content:
I adjusted TopLap's clock to compensate, and bam ! Upload to test succeeded. And kept succeeding henceforth.
This had blocked me for half a day ! Posts such as https://discord.com/channels/417796904760639509/948230185457696820/1004061088402387014 or https://discord.com/channels/417796904760639509/948230185457696820/1005104609620131890 were offering little hope.
I wouldn't be surprised if the issues listed here are related: https://discord.com/channels/417796904760639509/948230185457696820/1032313507728863324, https://discord.com/channels/417796904760639509/1047643035833479230/1154119278581256212, https://discord.com/channels/417796904760639509/420166863776120832/1143698973664759861, https://discord.com/channels/417796904760639509/948285944157593721/1126417702907555840, and more still !

Author: proteo4934
Content: If this is truly what is going on, I shudder to think of just how much of the general public wanting to join the wonderful lands of DCL might be woefully turned away at the front gate as a consequence âââ¢ââââââ¢ââ

Author: proteo4934
Content:
TLDR: @Peanutbutta, @meelrossi, @Kaze_no_Kai, the clocks on some of the servers are 1-2 minutes behind, which is very likely making a lot of crypto-signatures fail !
Arguably the proof: connection attempts finally succeed when setting the PC clock 2 minutes back.

Author: _cicadaa_
Content:
Hey, @Proteus. Thanks for your time in sharing your feedback with us. I truly understand how those issues affected your Decentraland experience, and I apologize on behalf of the team for the inconvenience. Please rest assured that we're continuously improving the platform to avoid similar issues in the future. I also highly recommend creating a post about your feedback here: https://decentraland.canny.io/world-explorer. Lastly, these intermittent issues are usually fixed by basic troubleshooting, such as clearing your browser's cache or reinstalling the desktop client. 

As for the WalletConnect issue you've been experiencing, we really appreciate the workaround you shared. Let me check with the team to confirm if there is something on the servers' time that causes the crypto signatures to fail. ð

Author: proteo4934
Content: You're welcome ! Hopefully DCL can inspire the telling of many more stories, with the initiatives such as https://www.zealous.co/decentraland/opportunity/wellness-week.

Author: kaze_no_kai
Content:
:dcl: Hello All,

To improve the experience using the platform we are making some changes in the urls used to access each one of our products. You may have noticed some of these changes already happening, moving some dapps from subdomains to paths (market.decentraland.org is now decentraland.org/marketplace)

Moving forward, we will be making the same change for the explorer. We are moving play.decentraland.org to **decentraland.org/play.** This may cause some pieces of your scenes or smart wearables to stop working due to CORS restrictions.

How do I know if this change will affect my scene or smart wearable?
1-  Check if any of those scenes or wearables have some interaction with an external source
2 - Check if any of the external sources have CORS enabled
If both of these are true, then make sure you enable decentraland.org domain as a valid domain to access it.
We already have decentraland.org/play url available so you will be able to test if your scene or wearable is working as expected and make the changes if not.

From **18th December**ðï¸ , we will be redirecting all the requests to play.decentraland.org to decentraland.org/play, so please make sure you have the changes before that date.

Thanks in advance for the support and let us know in case of any questions ð

Content: Hello whats the difference between a genesis land and world? What advantage do I have compared with someone that pays 100 mana for world?

Author: zigg.
Content: Hello! Decentraland Worlds are your individual 3D spaces within the Decentraland realm, separate from the primary Genesis City map. Your World can either be private or shared using a link, capable of hosting up to 100 peopleâideal for events or showcasing your creations. It acts as a personal canvas, providing a platform for your creativity to shine. The purchased land is where you bring your creations to life, implementing the scenes you've crafted within your Worlds. You can also visit this document to learn more about Worlds: https://docs.decentraland.org/creator/worlds/about/.

Author: kaze_no_kai
Content:
Hello All, in an effort to improve the user experience in the Foundation Discord :dcl: server, we have updated the channels structure, more details below: 

- We archived some of the channels if they are not longer applicable (editor-beta) or not used by most users (memes). 
- We have also renamed some channels and combined the content from others (releases notes is now product updates). 
- In addition we have enabled the Community Onboarding, you can check the options in the upper left corner (Channels and Role). 
- The Decentraland Foundation discord server can now be found when searching on the discord website.

**Detailed list of the changes we did:**

**Important section:**
- release-notes has been renamed to product-updates and you can find the information in the same channel from coming-soon, roadmap, all-hands and sdk-announcements
- faq has been updated with new content and official-links has been included in the same channel
- coming-soon, all-hands, roadmap, official-links have been archived
- sdk-announcements has been archived but still visible to all members

**Channels section:**
- video-and-streaming has been renamed to streaming
- art, feedback, memes, tools and hiring have been archived

**Support section:**
- making-wearables has been renamed to wearables-emotes-scenes
- editor-beta, desktop-beta, explorer, marketplace have been archived
- code-contributions and builder-and-3d have been archived but still visible for all members
- sdk has been archived but visible to all members
- sdk7-feedback has been renamed to sdk only

All these changes were done in an effort to improve the engagement and communication with all members.

Thank you in advance for the understanding ð

Author: _cicadaa_
Content: Hey, @PyrrhicVictory.eth. Welcome to Decentraland's Discord server. Please know that wearables and emotes in Decentraland reside on the Polygon network. Thus, they cannot be converted to Ethereum. Content:
Hello! I see you're having trouble with lag when accessing events in Decentraland. First, check if your computer meets the requirements here: https://docs.decentraland.org/player/general/hardware-requirements/. If it doesn't, the lag might be due to your computer. If it does meet the requirements, try these steps:
If using a browser, clear its cache or try a different one.
If using the desktop app, reinstall it and try again.

Let me know if the lag persists after trying these steps.

If you're using a desktop application, reinstall the application and try accessing Decentraland again. If the problem continues after trying these steps, please let me know.

You can start playing one of the most popular DG scenes in Decentraland, the ICE Poker, by clicking the "jump in" button on this page (https://decentraland.org/places/place/?position=-102.129) or using the /goto -102, 129 command via in-world chat. It may require you to have an ICE wearable to play. If you need more information about this scene, please contact Decentral Games directly. You can find the link to their Discord server here: https://docs.decentral.games/help/faq.

Author: _cicadaa_
Content: Hello, @Meanmanjr. Thanks for reaching out. I'm afraid we don't have control over the gas/transaction fees on the network, and it usually depends on the congestion of the network itself. That said, what I can suggest is to monitor the gas fees on gas tracker pages such as https://etherscan.io/gastracker. ð

Author: anialbano
Content: Hi @_Matt , QA Manager here. The team is in world all day long, besides we are constantly checking PRs, new features by requests, and the new explorer version is our testing priority. The fixes are out of our hands since it's not something we take care of. The dev team is more focused on severe bug reports at the moment and their capacity is limited. Regarding SDK, QA is starting to get into it right now and making a plan to augment our coverage.

Author: koa_matt
Content: Thank you @PixelPixie for the response and for providing visibility into the priorities. Personally, I would like to see the resolution of the many issues on the current platform become the priority before the introduction of more features. I understand that you are not responsible for fixing bugs, but you do have a responsibility to ensure that new features do not cause regression. In the past month or two we have had a lot of cool features released but with every release there seems to be a new bug or two introduced along with it. I don't want to be negative but this has been my experience lately.

Author: anialbano
Content: I totally understand your concerns! We are doing the best we can to prevent more problems and making regressions with each release. The QA team is brand new and even though we have experience with the platform, there are a lot of things to cover, but we are learning also from our mistakes, so thank you for addressing this. It helps us a lot to improve! If you have any concerns, you can find me here and in world with the same user name.

Content:
Hello @.Decentraland @Kaze_no_Kai 
Do we have any documentation on how to set up an AI powered chatbot in our lands? I have looked everywhere but couldn't find it, and we want to implement a conversational bot similar to the ones in the Genesis Plaza.

Author: _cicadaa_
Content: Hi, @Rodrigo Nunes. I understand you would like to put an AI NPC in your scene. Please check this GitHub repository to find our NPC toolkit that should help you achieve your plans for your scene: https://github.com/decentraland-scenes/dcl-npc-toolkit.

Author: _cicadaa_
Content: Thanks for the response, @Rodrigo Nunes. Those NPCs (Simone, Aisha, and Dodge) are powered by a backend service called Inworld. This blog post should give you more information about the NPCs in Genesis Plaza: https://decentraland.org/blog/announcements/ai-npcs-herald-the-beginning-of-ai-in-decentraland/#bringing-scenes-to-life-with-interactive-ai-npcs. I hope this information helps. ð

Author: thelord0125
Content:
ive been and am an active member there for 2 years. the bugs in talking about are due to dlc, not DG. when its their fault, yes i would talk to them. but many times its dlc fault. and worst is when its their fault they fix, when its dlc they do not.

i will give some examples, and obv dg team have more which u can ask. but im giving a rundown overall. 
so many times dlc makes updates to their server (sorry for any tecnical wrong word but the point is correct), and that messes ice game, sometimes dg doesnt get enough warnings, or upgrade done to dlc messes ice poker games and it has to be dlc to fix (in other words even if dg team wants to fix they cant). eventually dlc does it, but it takes to long.
soemtimes there is overall errors, like when game laggs bc "to many people" joinned an open chat. and there are several technicall problems that has to do with dlc, but most importantly, and this is the main point, dlc seems to lack the willingness to correct or to act fast. whatever might be the case, this is the impression i have. and i think dlc team knows its not a wrong idea i have, bc many times they failed, in my view, to help quickly fix ice poker problems.

ice poker in itself works well, the cards come out well, the rewards arrive to my wallet, their website and delegation works. ect ect. but seems building on dlc is an issue, and the support given by dlc team is lacking. for those reason i have the opinon i shared above

Author: metaversecrypto.
Content: I luv the renting ability! I wanna rent out my land but what kinda rights do tenants get? Can I cancel their lease at anytime? Can they rent it forever and never increase rent price. I don't wanna rent it out for $1 a day and be forced to rent it out forever at $1

Author: _cicadaa_
Content: Hi, @Metaverse $CRYPTO. I understand that you would like to rent out your land and would like to know more about the feature. When a user rents your land, they will have the operator permissions to your land. This means they will be able to deploy scenes to it, and cancelation of the tenant's lease is not possible. Regarding the rent period, it is up to you to decide how long the users can rent your land, and it's being set when you're listing your land for rent. You may also check this article to learn more about land rentals in Decentraland: https://docs.decentraland.org/player/market/rentals/.

Author: justin5266
Content:
Greetings Decentraland Community, @everyone

I'm excited to share with you my passion for creating custom wearables for the Decentraland metaverse! As a developer and designer, I have a strong vision for bringing your ideas to life and enhancing the virtual experience for all Decentraland users.

My goal is to collaborate with the community to design and implement unique wearables that reflect your individual style and creativity. Whether it's crafting eye-catching avatars, iconic accessories, or exclusive fashion items, I am committed to delivering high-quality, personalized wearables that will elevate the immersive world of Decentraland.

By combining cutting-edge technology with artistic flair, I aim to contribute to the diversity and vibrancy of the Decentraland metaverse. Let's work together to turn your concepts into stunning digital reality and make a lasting impact on the virtual landscape.

I look forward to connecting with you all and contributing to the evolution of Decentraland through innovative wearable designs. Together, we can make the metaverse a more vibrant and engaging place for all enthusiasts and explorers.

Warm regards,
Justin

Author: zigg.
Content: Yes, you can fetch all existing tokenIds for Decentraland parcels by interacting with the Decentraland smart contract on the Ethereum blockchain using tools like Web3.js or ethers.js. Query the contract to retrieve the list of tokenIds, then process the results accordingly. Remember to consider potential costs, such as gas fees, and scalability issues. Additionally, I advise conducting your own research (DYOR) on this matter.

Content:
Decentraland Art Week '24

Dear Decentraland Community Member,

Get ready to immerse yourself in a world of creativity as we kick off Decentraland Art Week '24! From March 26 to 29, we'll be showcasing the incredible artistic talent that flourishes within our virtual realm.

As we countdown to this exciting event, we invite you to join us in exploring the diverse array of artistic expressions that make Decentraland a vibrant and dynamic community.

In conjunction with this special occasion, we're glad to announce a token distribution exclusively for our early Decentraland users as a token of appreciation for their ongoing support and contribution to our platform's growth.

Author: _cicadaa_
Content:
Greetings, Decentraland Community! 

As we do our best to keep our Discord Community and the users safe from scammers and support team impersonators, we would like to remind you about the things to note to avoid getting victimized by a FAKE Support/Scammer on our Discord server. 

Please note that **a legitimate member of our Support Team will *NOT***:
- Ask you to access a suspicious link to open a ticket with us,
- Create a ticket for you outside our Discord server, 
- Ask you to verify yourself using your wallet or account information,
- Provide assistance via Direct Messages (DMs) or DM you first.

If you received a suspicious DM or response from someone regarding your concerns/inquiries, please:
- Avoid providing sensitive account-related information, 
- Take a screenshot of the conversation and report it on the #report-scam channel.

We will look into your report/s and take appropriate actions against the reported user when necessary. Let's keep our Discord server a safe community for everyone. Thank you all!

On that note, please know that we have the #ð·ðº-russian language channel you may utilize if you're more comfortable speaking with the community using your native language. Regarding your inquiry, there are lots of things you can do in Decentraland. You can meet other users and hang out with them in different places or events in Decentraland. You can also win free wearables and emotes by participating in the events or playing the games on the platform (please check the in-world Discover page by pressing the "X" button on your keyboard or by accessing this page on your browser https://places.decentraland.org/places/genesis/). Those wearables and emotes are NFTs, which means you can sell them on the marketplace. 

On the other hand, you may also be a content creator and monetize your content by creating and publishing your wearable and emote collections and developing a scene in Decentraland. Here's the link to our Docs page for complete guidance: https://docs.decentraland.org/creator/.

Author: catadecruz
Content: Hi, there is a few approaches you could utilize to make events private. Access through certain wallet addresses, certain held NFT or token are likely the most common ones. Requiring your participants to share their address upfront or having the NFT in the wallet they connect with. As well you could make use of codes for a door thats required upon entering a certain area. It will generally depend on the way your participants join the platform and the skillset you or the developer of your choice comes with. This GitHub repository shares a few approaches: https://github.com/decentraland-scenes/Awesome-Repository

Author: catadecruz
Content: Hey, lowering the graphic settings, will generally help, decreasing scene load radius will have a big impact. Using the desktop client offers typically a better performance in comparison to the browser version too. As well, loading will vary heavily, depending on the area you load in and the populated LAND surrounding you.

Content:
ð Hi All, just wanted to mention that there have been a lot of scammers recently. Just want to point out few common scams:

â â â 
Scammers will try to approach you on a DM - the Support team will NEVER do that!
Scammers may sent a link to join a "Ticket" - the Support team will create a ticket for you which will be visible in this server, no need to click on any links!
Scammers will try to impersonate Support members by including Support or Mod in their profile, look for a Support role instead!

In case of any doubts, please be extra careful and let us know!

Author: _cicadaa_
Content: Hello, @Noam33. Renting out LAND you own is indeed one way to earn in Decentraland. You can list your LAND for rent and set a rental price (in MANA) per day for it. The price per day times the number of days in the period is what the tenant will pay upfront and in total for that rent. Here's the complete guide for it: https://docs.decentraland.org/player/market/rentals/.

Author: anonyking.
Content: And decentraland metaverse is like Roblox? I mean does it costs internet data to load a world?

Author: sinfulmeatstick
Content:
On decentraland if you would like to to have a world you would have to purchase a name it costs 100 mana + eth gas fee. 

With a name you have access to your own world where you can use up to 90k parcels worth of space to build on, 100 vp in the Decentraland dao , a sub domain, and a unique name you can wear on the decentraland metaverse platform

Author: sinfulmeatstick
Content:
To build on a world you, could use the decentraland builder which I belive has not been worked on in a while , or have knowledge using blender, Javascript, and SDK7. 

There is another solution that is currently being developed by a group community coders called called  inworld builder which could be our no code solution for building on decentraland 

Or you could hire one of the meny amazing g studios here on decentraland to make your vision come to reality

Author: eldanak_dcl
Content: Hi again everyone, we have an update regarding the Rave Mode issue. Although we do not have a fix yet, we have a few workaround to offer should you experience this issue. If you use Chrome or Firefox, we advise to lower the scene load radius to 2 (or 1 for scenes with lot of assets), this helps reducing the occurence of the issue. You can also try  on opera GX browser ð Additionnaly you can use the desktop version (remember, with the Social Log In you do not need to have your wallet on your phone anymore!).

Content: Hey @Proteus, I'm afraid there's not, and we're not planning to.
